      "equal_temperament_12_notes_per_octave_": "Equal temperament: octave pakhat ah note 12, ratio 2^(1/12). A4 = 440 Hz; A5 = 880 Hz. Bach nih Well-Tempered Clavier (1722) nih vawlei kha hi compromise ah a i thlaih ter. Hika na tukmi note paoh cu cu grid cungah an um.",
      "scales_the_major_minor_modal_grammar": "Scales — major + minor + modal grammar",
      "major_w_w_h_w_w_w_h_minor_w_h_w_w_h_w_": "Major: W-W-H-W-W-W-H. Minor: W-H-W-W-H-W-W. Modes 7 (Ionian, Dorian, Phrygian, Lydian, Mixolydian, Aeolian, Locrian) cu major scale interval pattern lehnak in an rat.",
      "chords_stacked_thirds_inversions": "Chords — stacked thirds + inversions",
      "triads_root_third_fifth_major_4_3_semi": "Triads: root + third + fifth. Major (4+3 semitones), minor (3+4), diminished (3+3), augmented (4+4). 7th chords nih third dang an chiah. Pop music = ~chords 6 an i cang; jazz nih extensions le substitutions a hman.",
      "harmony_pad_voiced_pads_drones": "Harmony Pad — voiced pads + drones",
      "sustained_chord_textures_the_bed_under": "Sustained chord textures — cinematic score paoh a niang i ihkhun. Minor ah iv-V-i, asiloah Hans Zimmer ruahnak awkah i-VI-VII zuam. Fifths ah drones nih India classical music le bagpipe phunglam an bawmh.",
      "beat_pad_sample_based_drums": "Beat Pad — sample-based drums",
      "most_popular_music_sits_at_4_4_90_130_": "Music a hlawhtling deuh cu 4/4, 90-130 BPM ah an um. Hip-hop ~85-95, house 120-130, drum-and-bass ~170 (half-time ruahnak). Kick 1+3 ah, snare 2+4 ah = backbeat — rock + pop i hram.",
      "theory_the_math_behind_the_sound": "Theory — aw hnu ah math",
      "pythagoras_500_bce_discovered_consonan": "Pythagoras (~BCE 500) nih integer frequency ratios in consonance a hmuh: octave 2:1, fifth 3:2, fourth 4:3. Helmholtz nih 1862 ah a karhter. Aw = compression waves; music = a dawh tiah kan i thlahmi pattern.",
